
The code runs on Matlab and requires the Psychtoolbox (http://psychtoolbox.org/).

The center piece is the function BangorGamblingTask_ENGL, which runs one session of the task. To run, this function calls the following:

- GetBGTPaySequences (function)
- settings_BangorGamblingTask_ENGL (script)
- GetSubjectInfo_ENGL (function)
- saveBehavData (function)

After execution, BangorGamblingTask_ENGL saves two files, a *.txt and a *.mat, containing the behavioral data recorded.
